"Design principle" = "Design principle";
"If Mel Tejo ever feels like it could be swapped onto another random sport, it is not specific enough. Atlas mode protects against that." = "If Mel Tejo ever feels like it could be swapped onto another random sport, it is not specific enough. Atlas mode protects against that.";
"Roots of Tejo" = "Roots of Tejo";
"Why this Colombian sport feels heavy, ritualistic, and unlike a generic target game." = "Why this Colombian sport feels heavy, ritualistic, and unlike a generic target game.";
"3 min read" = "3 min read";
"A sport built around impact" = "A sport built around impact";
"Tejo is not about soft accuracy alone. It is a tactile throwing sport built around clay, metal, distance, and the emotional build-up before contact. That makes it feel more physical and ceremonial than many mobile-friendly sports concepts." = "Tejo is not about soft accuracy alone. It is a tactile throwing sport built around clay, metal, distance, and the emotional build-up before contact. That makes it feel more physical and ceremonial than many mobile-friendly sports concepts.";
"Why Colombia matters here" = "Why Colombia matters here";
"Mel Tejo keeps the sport anchored in Colombia because that context gives the game its identity. Without that cultural grounding, tejo would risk feeling like just another abstract disc-throwing mechanic." = "Mel Tejo keeps the sport anchored in Colombia because that context gives the game its identity. Without that cultural grounding, tejo would risk feeling like just another abstract disc-throwing mechanic.";
"Why Mel uses a premium tone" = "Why Mel uses a premium tone";
"The app translates the weight of clay and steel into a premium visual language. The goal is not to turn tejo into something luxurious for its own sake, but to respect the drama, pressure, and sensory presence that already exist inside the sport." = "The app translates the weight of clay and steel into a premium visual language. The goal is not to turn tejo into something luxurious for its own sake, but to respect the drama, pressure, and sensory presence that already exist inside the sport.";
"How a Throw Works" = "How a Throw Works";
"A quick internal guide to the logic behind power, arc, composure, and premium hits in Mel Tejo." = "A quick internal guide to the logic behind power, arc, composure, and premium hits in Mel Tejo.";
"2 min read" = "2 min read";
"Power" = "Power";
"Power shapes whether the disc arrives with enough intent to threaten the ring instead of fading out. Too little and the throw drifts. Too much and the release can feel rushed unless the rest of the motion is balanced." = "Power shapes whether the disc arrives with enough intent to threaten the ring instead of fading out. Too little and the throw drifts. Too much and the release can feel rushed unless the rest of the motion is balanced.";
"Arc and composure" = "Arc and composure";
"Arc changes the feeling of the landing, while composure represents how controlled the release is under pressure. In Mel Tejo, premium results come from balance. The cleanest throws happen when force, shape, and calm all align." = "Arc changes the feeling of the landing, while composure represents how controlled the release is under pressure. In Mel Tejo, premium results come from balance. The cleanest throws happen when force, shape, and calm all align.";
"Reading the results" = "Reading the results";
"Drift means the throw never really took shape. Mecha and mano show progress and control. Bocin is the premium center-ring hit, while moñona is the crown result that marks a decisive, high-pressure finish." = "Drift means the throw never really took shape. Mecha and mano show progress and control. Bocin is the premium center-ring hit, while moñona is the crown result that marks a decisive, high-pressure finish.";
"Session Rituals" = "Session Rituals";
"What the Session Deck is actually tracking, and how a night of throws turns into a story." = "What the Session Deck is actually tracking, and how a night of throws turns into a story.";
"Progress comes from Throw Lab" = "Progress comes from Throw Lab";
"Session Deck does not advance on its own. It listens to what you do inside Throw Lab. Every completed throw updates your live stats, and those stats feed the active ritual card." = "Session Deck does not advance on its own. It listens to what you do inside Throw Lab. Every completed throw updates your live stats, and those stats feed the active ritual card.";
"Each card watches a different metric" = "Each card watches a different metric";
"Some cards track premium hits, some watch for a moñona, and others care about flow. Flow means consecutive scoring throws without a drift breaking the streak. This makes each card feel like a different kind of night, not just a different score target." = "Some cards track premium hits, some watch for a moñona, and others care about flow. Flow means consecutive scoring throws without a drift breaking the streak. This makes each card feel like a different kind of night, not just a different score target.";
"Why this exists" = "Why this exists";
"The point of Session Deck is to frame a session with intention. Instead of opening the app and throwing randomly, you choose a mood for the night: confidence, precision, spectacle, or consistency." = "The point of Session Deck is to frame a session with intention. Instead of opening the app and throwing randomly, you choose a mood for the night: confidence, precision, spectacle, or consistency.";
